{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an AI assistant that provides information on national cybersecurity strategies and related resources."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Can you give me some details about resources related to national cybersecurity strategies?"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Certainly! Here are some resources related to national cybersecurity strategies:\n\n1. Potomac Institute for Policy Studies - 'Cyber Readiness Index 2.0', 2015. This report can be accessed at https://www.potomacinstitute.org/images/CRIndex2.0.pdf and provides insight into the readiness of various nations in terms of their cybersecurity capabilities.\n\n2. CCDCOE - 'Cybersecurity Strategy & Governance Repository'. This repository, available at https://ccdcoe.org/library/strategy-and-governance/, is a comprehensive collection of strategies and governance documents from different countries.\n\n3. ENISA - 'National Capabilities Assessment Framework', 2020. This framework provides an assessment of national capabilities in cybersecurity.\n\n4. Global Cyber Security Capacity Centre - 'Cybersecurity Capacity Maturity Model for Nations (CMM)', Dimension 1: 1.1, University of Oxford, 2021. More details can be found at https://gcscc.ox.ac.uk/cmm-2021-edition.\n\n5. OAS - 'Managing National Cyber Risk', 2018. This document, available at https://www.oas.org/es/sms/cicte/ENGcyberrisk.pdf, offers insights into managing national cybersecurity risks.\n\n6. ENISA - 'National Cyber Security Strategies: Training Tool', 2016. This tool is designed to aid in the development and implementation of national cybersecurity strategies.\n\nThese resources offer valuable information for developing and assessing national cybersecurity strategies."}]}
